content:
The Q1 2020 net income stood at $99.6 million as compared to $143.5 million in Q1 2019, according to financial results <a href="https://investor.signatureny.com/file/Index?KeyFile=403704865" data-v-f87c67ca="">published</a> on Thursday. Signature Bank said the drop in net income is due to an increase in the provision for credit losses of $60.5 million.<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
The provision for the losses "was wholly attributable to COVID-19," said the bank.&nbsp;
